# department-templates.http
# Testes manuais do CRUD de templates de departamentos (SUPER_ADMIN)
# Requer um token de acesso SUPER_ADMIN em @token.
#
# Uso com VS Code REST Client ou JetBrains HTTP Client.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@token = <COLOQUE_SEU_TOKEN_SUPER_ADMIN_AQUI>

### 1. Login (obter token SUPER_ADMIN)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "super@dmdoc.io",
  "password": "senha_do_super_admin"
}

### 2. Criar template simples (2 nós)
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/department-templates
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "Estrutura Padrão RH",
  "description": "Template de departamentos para empresas com RH estruturado",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "refId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
      "parentRefId": null,
      "name": "Recursos Humanos",
      "tags": ["rh"]
    },
    {
      "refId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002",
      "parentRefId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
      "name": "Folha de Pagamento",
      "tags": ["folha", "financeiro"]
    }
  ]
}

### 3. Listar templates (primeira página)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/department-templates
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 4. Listar templates com paginação
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/department-templates?limit=5&cursor=<nextCursor>
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. Detalhe de um template
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/department-templates/<id-do-template>
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6. Atualizar nome e descrição
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/admin/department-templates/<id-do-template>
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "Estrutura Padrão RH v2",
  "description": "Versão atualizada do template de RH"
}

### 7. Atualizar nodes (valida parentRefIds)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/admin/department-templates/<id-do-template>
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "nodes": [
    {
      "refId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
      "parentRefId": null,
      "name": "Recursos Humanos",
      "tags": ["rh"]
    },
    {
      "refId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002",
      "parentRefId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
      "name": "Recrutamento",
      "tags": []
    },
    {
      "refId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000003",
      "parentRefId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
      "name": "Treinamento",
      "tags": []
    }
  ]
}

### 8. Erro esperado: parentRefId aponta para refId inexistente (deve retornar 422)
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/department-templates
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "Template Inválido",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "refId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000010",
      "parentRefId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000099",
      "name": "Departamento Órfão",
      "tags": []
    }
  ]
}

### 9. Erro esperado: nome duplicado (deve retornar 409)
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/department-templates
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "Estrutura Padrão RH v2",
  "nodes": []
}

### 10. Excluir template (hard delete)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/admin/department-templates/<id-do-template>
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 11. Erro esperado: template inexistente (deve retornar 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/department-templates/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
